						               													<description>This is a children game from Spear's. It does not use a battery , but a ball bearing  to get the doors and traps moving. The horror theme is always attractive to kids.&amp;#10;Each player tries to go from the bottom to top of the 3D castle. Each time a piece lands in a white square, the player must press hard on it in order to release the ball. The ball will fall down and on its way through certain doors and traps will &amp;quot;flick&amp;quot; hitting the players pieces. Those hit pieces will fall from the Castle and need to start again !!&amp;#10;Look the pictures and rules, and you can figure it out quickly.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The &amp;quot;magic&amp;quot; part, is that the ball, can follow 3 different ways of coming down... so flicking different traps and doors each time accordingly. Therefore, some shouting and excitement, and if lucky relief, when standing in a dangerous place and you hear the ball coming down...it could be you!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
